UserPreferencesUpdatedEvent is fired if users navigates to profile page and changes his timezone. But it is not fired when user changes his time zone by clicking the link on the time zone mismatch warning notification. I have attached the screenshot of this notification.
 !tz-warning.png|thumbnail!
*This cause our work log calculations to ignore users latest time zone changes and cause invalid timesheet to be shown.*

Also this event does not allows you to get user key, it only returns username which may be changed. Not important for our case but it should also be changed for consistency.
{code}
    @SuppressWarnings("unused")
    @com.atlassian.event.api.EventListener
    public void onUserPreferencesUpdate(UserPreferencesUpdatedEvent userPreferencesUpdatedEvent) {
        String usernameOfAffectedUser = userPreferencesUpdatedEvent.getUsername();
        ApplicationUser affectedUser = userManager.getUserByName(usernameOfAffectedUser);
        TZHistory latestTimeZoneOfUser = getLatestTimeZoneOfUser(affectedUser);
        recordTimeZoneHistoryIfDoesNotMatch(affectedUser, latestTimeZoneOfUser);
    }
{code}

